      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/2/52",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ اَلْمُحْرِمُ يَنْزِعُ اَلْحَشِيشَ مِنْ غَيْرِ اَلْحَرَمِ فَقَالَ «نَعَمْ» قُلْتُ فَمِنَ اَلْحَرَمِ قَالَ «لاَ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2346 - It has been narrated from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from one of the Imams (as), who said:\nI asked him: \"Can a person in the state of ihram remove grass from outside the Haram?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Yes.\"\nI then asked: \"What about from within the Haram?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"No.\""
        ]
      }
    },
